@startuml match-status-state-diagram

title Match Status — State Diagram

[*] --> SCHEDULED : match created

SCHEDULED --> IN_PROGRESS : match starts
SCHEDULED --> POSTPONED : match postponed
SCHEDULED --> CANCELLED : match cancelled\nbefore start

IN_PROGRESS --> COMPLETED : match ends\n(home_goals + away_goals set)
IN_PROGRESS --> SUSPENDED : match interrupted
IN_PROGRESS --> FORFEITED : forfeit declared\nduring match

SUSPENDED --> IN_PROGRESS : match resumes
SUSPENDED --> COMPLETED : resumed and finished
SUSPENDED --> CANCELLED : not replayed
SUSPENDED --> FORFEITED : forfeit declared\nafter suspension

POSTPONED --> SCHEDULED : rescheduled
POSTPONED --> CANCELLED : not replayed
POSTPONED --> FORFEITED : forfeit declared\nafter postponement

CANCELLED --> [*]
COMPLETED --> [*]
FORFEITED --> [*]

note right of COMPLETED
  home_goals and away_goals
  are meaningful only in
  COMPLETED and IN_PROGRESS
end note

note right of FORFEITED
  Score is stored explicitly:
  home_goals=3, away_goals=0 → home team wins
  home_goals=0, away_goals=3 → away team wins
  No separate field needed.
end note

@enduml
